parameters: \n<Roselitte>"I refuse. I will not quit being a knight."

\n<Yuri>"What do you plan to do by going to the battlefield as the
Crown Prince's wife? Father will never allow it."

\n<Roselitte>"I protest... No matter what you say, Lord Yuri, even if
it's His Majesty himself, I will go where I must."

\n<Roselitte>"No matter what you say, it's fine. I have no intention of
quitting being a knight, no matter what."

\n<Roselitte>"If you insist on making me quit, then the engagement too...
I shall have it annulled."

Roselitte raised her voice while caressing the engagement
ring on her finger.
\n<Roselitte>"The ring you gave me... I will... return it to you!"

\n<Yuri>"...Alright, I understand. If you say so, then I'll take it
back."
Roselitte quickly brushed away Yuri's outstretched hand.

\n<Yuri>"...Sigh. Alright, I understand. We'll revisit this matter
later. But promise me just this one thing."

\n<Yuri>"You take a break for a while. Once I finish this expedition
mission, I'll take some time off as well."
\n<Yuri>"Ah, that's right. An early honeymoon wouldn't be too bad."
\n<Yuri>"...What do you think? It's not a bad idea, right?"

\n<Roselitte>"We should head back soon. If we're apart for too long, it
will cause unnecessary worry among the soldiers."
\n<Yuri>"You want to go back already? We still have time."

\n<Roselitte>"No, it's not allowed. You must follow my instructions
regarding your safety, Lord Yuri."
\n<Yuri>"...Such a stubborn knight can be quite troublesome."
\n<Yuri>"Then let's take our time returning... Come here."
\n<Yuri>"...That was close. Sorry about that, Rosel--"
\n<Yuri>"No way... What in the world is happening!?"
\n<Roselitte>"Damn... Hurry to the village! I'll carve us a path!"
